race.comment: LES BRAVES (3) is knocking on the door and finds a suitable race here. He's just found one better the past three times he's stepped out, going down by a nose over this track and distance last time out. Jamie Mott goes aboard here having provided his sole win to date and he won't need to do any more to be taking care of these. THUNDER HAWK (9) ran well fresh at Cranbourne, tackling a stronger race second up at Flemington and struggling. Back in trip here is a slight niggle but she's up to winning this. MAGIC MONEY (10) was a narrow maiden winner fresh and okay up to this grade at Mornington second up. He can continue to progress. HOT CHIPS (2) stuck on well fresh at Mornington when in the market and will be fitter for that.
